# Console UI (agent guide)

Applies when planning or implementing anything under `src/app/console/`. Compose from existing components; do not invent new nav or tab patterns.

## Principles

- **One question per screen** (e.g. “Who is on the team?”, “How is this app set up?”).
- **Plain language.** Short labels. **No em-dashes** in UI copy.
- **Reuse before inventing.** Match Home, Apps, Team, and Profile.
- **shadcn first** — see `.cursor/rules/shadcn-ui.mdc`. Primitives only in `components/ui/` (CLI).

## Information architecture

| Daily nav | Route |
|-----------|-------|
| Home | `/` |
| Apps | `/apps` |
| Team | `/team` |

Everything else (Settings, Activity, security, etc.) → **Search** (⌘K) or contextual links. **Not** inline header links.

Primary nav: **org menu** (chevron next to org name) via `OrgNavMenu`.

## Header (`AppHeader.tsx`)

Three-column grid on all breakpoints:

```
[ Org ▼ + breadcrumbs ]   [ Search ]   [ Account ]
```

| Zone | Rule |
|------|------|
| Org + menu | Name links home; chevron → Home · Apps · Team |
| Breadcrumbs | `HeaderBreadcrumbs` — truncate; `…` dropdown when long; never push search/profile off-screen |
| Search | Mobile: icon. `md+`: “Search or jump to…” bar. Same `ConsoleSearch` dialog |
| Account | Avatar menu; `shrink-0` always visible |

Do **not** add: second nav row, hamburger sidebars, full-width mobile search competing with org name.

## Page patterns (pick one per module)

| Pattern | When | Components |
|---------|------|------------|
| **Hub** | Landing / overview | Metric cards (3-col grid), next-step cards — `HomeView` |
| **List** | Record index | `ListPageHeader` + `DataTable` |
| **List tabs** | Two sibling lists on one page only | `ResourceTabs` (e.g. Members \| Invites) |
| **Workspace** | Multi-section entity | Header + **`SectionSidebar`** + `<Outlet />` |
| **Detail** | Single view, no sections | `EntityDetailLayout` without tabs |

**Never** use horizontal `PageTabBar` / line `TabsList` for entity sections. Use `SectionSidebar`.

### Workspace layout

```
[ Avatar / title / subtitle / badges / actions ]

[ SectionSidebar ]   [ content ]
```

- Desktop: vertical sidebar. Mobile: horizontal scroll (same component).
- Active link: `bg-muted`, not underline tabs.
- App: `AppWorkspaceLayout` + `AppSectionSidebar`
- Profile: `ProfileLayout` + `SectionSidebar`

References: `AppWorkspaceLayout.tsx`, `ProfileLayout.tsx`, `SectionSidebar.tsx`

## Data tables (`DataTable.tsx`)

- Toolbar (search, columns) and pagination **inside** the table `Card`.
- Toolbar + column headers share muted top band.

## Forms

- `FormField`; labels above inputs; errors on the field.
- Destructive actions → `ConfirmDialog`.
- No bloated intros.

## Copy

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| “Set up email” | “Configure your SMTP integration —” |
| “No members yet” | Long explanatory empty states |
| “Team”, “Apps”, “Home” | Internal module names in UI |

Metrics: **bold numbers**; status tokens (`Off`, `On`, `Test`), not sentences.

## Responsive checklist (~390px and ~1024px)

- Org name, search, account all visible
- Breadcrumbs truncate/collapse; search and profile never clipped
- `SectionSidebar` scrolls horizontally on mobile
- Metric cards stay 3 columns unless intentional

## Component map

| Need | Path |
|------|------|
| Shell | `components/shell/AppShell.tsx`, `AppHeader.tsx` |
| Org nav | `components/shell/OrgNavMenu.tsx` |
| Search | `components/shell/ConsoleSearch.tsx` |
| Breadcrumbs | `components/shell/HeaderBreadcrumbs.tsx` |
| Section nav | `components/layout/SectionSidebar.tsx` |
| App workspace | `components/apps/AppWorkspaceLayout.tsx` |
| List header | `components/crud/ListPageHeader.tsx` |
| Table | `components/crud/DataTable.tsx` |
| List sub-views | `components/crud/ResourceTabs.tsx` |
| Detail header | `components/layout/EntityDetailLayout.tsx` |

## New module checklist

1. Pick a page pattern above.
2. Register route in `routes.tsx`; add `SEARCH_ITEMS` / breadcrumbs if needed.
3. Multi-section → `SectionSidebar` only (no new tab styles).
4. Update console e2e if nav paths change.
